article.description: Sam Houston St. 72, Tex San Antonio 56
article.headline: Sam Houston St. 72, Tex San Antonio 56
article.linkText: Sam Houston St. 72, Tex San Antonio 56
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Joe Thompson scored 14 points and Chris Jordan and Ryan Bright each added 13 points and eight rebounds to lead Sam Houston State to a 72-56 victory over Texas-San Antonio on Thursday night. Sam Houston State (12-8, 6-2 Southland Conference) led 33-25 at the half and used an 18-0 run over a five-minute stretch to take a 62-38 lead with 6:45 left. Wilder Auguste added 12 points for Sam Houston State. Andre Owens led Texas-San Antonio (9-9, 4-3) with 18 points and four steals. John Millsap had 17 rebounds.
